1
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:33,960
Come here.

2
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:38,160
Pound!

3
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:42,000
Peace is about to cross the street.
How is it over there?

4
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:10,080
- Please step back!
- Don't leave me!

5
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:13,120
- Stop! Let me go!
- What the hell is happening?

6
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:14,960
Peace!

7
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:16,280
Calm down!

8
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:20,400
Peace!

9
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:22,520
Peace!

10
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:29,160
Peace!

11
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:31,880
Peace…

12
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:35,000
No way!

13
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:43,880
<i>Have you ever wondered why we're alive?</i>

14
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:47,520
Why are we studying?

15
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:50,760
Fuang!

16
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:53,000
Why are you getting all philosophical now?

17
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:55,200
- Yeah.
- You gotta think.

18
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:59,240
We've graduated from high school,
and soon we'll finish college too.

19
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:02,520
Gotta start thinking ahead!

20
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:06,160
What's the big deal, Fuang?

21
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:09,600
We work, get married, have a nice family.

22
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:10,720
That's it.

23
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:13,680
Yuan, you're such a family man.

24
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:14,600
Yeah.

25
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:18,400
No way! Life shouldn't be that boring.

26
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:22,680
I'm taking my family business global.
Just watch!

27
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,160
Wow!

28
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:26,480
Global!

29
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,880
But!

30
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:32,320
I'm definitely not running
my parents' canned fish factory.

31
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:33,960
So boring!

32
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:35,800
Whoa, Franc!

33
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:39,280
You and Pound don't even have to work
and you're already rich.

34
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:41,680
- Yeah, right.
- Hey. No.

35
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:45,400
If you're gonna get rich,
you have to do it yourself.

36
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:47,480
Listen.

37
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:49,920
- What is it?
- And I'm telling you.

38
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:53,560
When I get rich, just tell me

39
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:57,560
what you want to do.
I'll invest. We'll all get rich together!

40
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:00,080
Whoa, Boss Pound!

41
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:04,000
- Boss Pound!
- Boss Pound!

42
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:05,800
- Hey!
- Don't come any closer!

43
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:09,240
Wait! If we work together,
can we promise one thing?

44
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:11,880
- What?
- If we work together,

45
00:04:12,480 --> 00:04:15,520
we won't fight over money.

46
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:18,160
Don't worry.

47
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:21,079
Money will never come between us.

48
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:26,320
Hey, you guys!

49
00:04:26,400 --> 00:04:28,680
- Huh?
- Can we make one more promise?

50
00:04:28,760 --> 00:04:29,800
- What?
- What?

51
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:33,880
When we're grown-ups,
no fighting over boys, alright?

52
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:35,160
- Huh?
- Huh?

53
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:42,080
I mean, in case Pound and Yuan
like the same guy,

54
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:43,960
they won't stop being friends
because of a boy.

55
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:46,280
- I see.
- Hey!

56
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:48,360
- What do we do?
- Mr. Pound.

57
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:50,520
- Whoa!
- You guys!

58
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:53,040
- You've got it all wrong!
- Come on, everyone! Get ready!

59
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:54,640
- Hurry.
- Alright, come on.

60
00:04:57,600 --> 00:05:01,640
Hey, Peace invited us to celebrate
at his new house. Are you coming with me?

61
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:02,920
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

62
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:07,640
Come on in, everyone! Welcome!

63
00:05:09,960 --> 00:05:10,800
What a huge house!

64
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:14,560
He's here. Everyone,
give our host a proper welcome!

65
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:23,880
Congrats. I'm happy for all of you.

66
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:26,480
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

67
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:30,240
Peace, your house is beautiful.
Even nicer than the pictures you sent me.

68
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:31,760
Why did he send you the pictures?

69
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:32,960
Yeah, why?

70
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,440
No, I mean…

71
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:37,800
He was asking about home decor.

72
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:41,560
My mom knows
some antique and collectible shops,

73
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:44,400
so he sent the photos to my mom
to help pick things.

74
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:46,160
- Oh.
- Yeah.

75
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:48,480
That's it. You're all flustered!

76
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:49,760
Yuan!

77
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:53,760
Peace, how much is this place?

78
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,440
Probably around fifty…

79
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:58,640
Fifty million plus.

80
00:05:58,720 --> 00:06:01,240
- What?
- In cash, everyone!

81
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:03,480
See that? No college degree,

82
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:05,640
and he got rich selling fried durian.

83
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:10,080
You're my top senior, my idol.
I love you, man!

84
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:13,320
- Hey, you're crazy!
- Now I'm craving fried durian!

85
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:14,920
- Hey, guys!
- What's up? You scared me!

86
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,760
- What?
- Swimming pool!

87
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:17,880
- Where?
- Look!

88
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:20,520
- Let's check it out.
- I thought it was something!

89
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:22,600
- I got scared too.
- Yeah.

90
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:25,600
Peace, can I use the bathroom?

91
00:06:26,520 --> 00:06:29,320
- Sure, I'll show you.
- Thank you.

92
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:34,920
Pound!

93
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,080
Yeah?

94
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:38,480
Let's check out the pool together.

95
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:41,320
Come on. I've never seen this pool either.
It's amazing.

96
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:43,360
- What? I've already seen it!
- Let's go see it!

97
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,800
Peace, you still kept this?

98
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:57,880
Wow!

99
00:06:57,960 --> 00:07:00,720
I drew it so quickly back then.

100
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:06,640
You even framed it so nicely.

101
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:12,600
If you're going to frame it like this,
should I redraw it so it looks perfect?

102
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:18,120
No need to make it perfect.
The way it is now,

103
00:07:19,080 --> 00:07:20,120
I like it.

104
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:27,080
I have something for you too.

105
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,360
What is it?

106
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:38,040
Close your eyes.

107
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:43,360
Okay.

108
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,400
Open your eyes.

109
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,880
Congrats.

110
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:07,440
Thank you!

111
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:15,040
It's so cute!

112
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,400
Let me put it on you.

113
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:48,240
No! Don't do that!

114
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:56,120
Let's go find my friends.

115
00:08:58,880 --> 00:09:01,160
Okay.

116
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:12,280
- Hey!
- Hold on!

117
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:14,760
You guys didn't wait at all!

118
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,560
- Hurry, get in the pool!
- Get in!

119
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:17,760
Come on, jump in!

120
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,040
Get in the pool. Jump!

121
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:20,840
- Jump!
- Jump!

122
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:23,000
- Jump!
- Jump!

123
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:26,360
- Jump!
- Hurry, we're waiting!

124
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,280
I'm ready!

125
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:29,440
- Take off your shoes and get in!
- Come on!

126
00:09:29,520 --> 00:09:31,520
- Get in!
- Hurry!

127
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:33,320
Get in the pool! Jump!

128
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:35,880
Come down quickly! Jump!

129
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:40,120
- Yay!
- Hey!

130
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:43,640
- Yes!
- Look over here. Let's take a picture!

131
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:45,600
- Hey, Pound, Yuan!
- Yay!

132
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:46,800
- Yes!
- Hey!

133
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:47,880
Yuan, Pound!

134
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:50,120
Pound, Yuan, come on!

135
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,440
Yeah!

136
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:21,240
Hello.

137
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:26,040
Cent, I've decided. I'm returning
the company shares to you.

138
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:27,920
Returning the shares to me?

139
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:31,240
Yes, returning them without selling.

140
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:33,760
<i>I'm not taking a single baht from you.</i>

141
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:36,160
Is there a but, Mom?

142
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:37,320
SOM TAM PALACE

143
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:38,320
There is.

144
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:41,720
You'll have to do something
for me in return.

145
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:42,920
<i>What do you want me to do?</i>

146
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:49,920
We just met. Aren't you going to ask
how I've been?

147
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,640
You're already healthy.

148
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:53,320
Nothing's guaranteed, you know.

149
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,880
What do I have to do for the shares?

150
00:10:55,520 --> 00:10:59,920
I want you to do something
that makes day-to-day workers richer.

151
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,160
I'm not a lottery operator!

152
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:04,240
Then use that tech of yours
that makes others rich!

153
00:11:05,520 --> 00:11:08,880
And you'll have to do the work
here in Thailand.

154
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:14,040
Don't hire anyone or let your staff do it.

155
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:17,400
You have to do it yourself,
right in front of me.

156
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:18,400
No way!

157
00:11:23,800 --> 00:11:26,480
Otherwise, I'll sell the shares!
I gave you the money to invest.

158
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:28,800
I thought that once you got rich,
you'd work less.

159
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:31,440
But no. You get richer and just work more!

160
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:34,560
I'm old, I could drop dead any day.

161
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:36,120
I don't want to die hugging money.

162
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:39,480
Mom! But your challenge isn't easy.

163
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:41,280
Technology for people who make ends meet?

164
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:44,160
With just making a living each day,
their time's already gone.

165
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:45,720
They don't have time to--

166
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,960
When the time comes,
they can learn on their own.

167
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:51,080
There's nothing humans can't learn.

168
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:56,000
And you have to make your technology
reach them.

169
00:11:56,600 --> 00:11:59,600
Otherwise, I'll sell
the shares to someone else.

170
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:05,320
<i>Mom's challenge is insanely tough.</i>
<i>Truly out of this world.</i>

171
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:08,960
Yeah! It's huge and overwhelming!

172
00:12:12,240 --> 00:12:13,880
But you have to make it work!

173
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:16,080
Your mom's shares are crucial to us, Cent.

174
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:20,760
If we get them,
we stay major shareholders.

175
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:24,520
But if the VC gets them,
they'll take over our company.

176
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:28,400
- Take over?
- Exactly!

177
00:12:29,520 --> 00:12:33,160
But if we get your mom's shares,
that problem disappears.

178
00:12:33,960 --> 00:12:37,920
Here's the plan.
You handle your mom's business.

179
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:41,760
<i>I'll take care of Japan and Singapore.</i>
<i>Don't worry.</i>

180
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:46,680
So I really have to do this, huh?

181
00:12:46,760 --> 00:12:47,640
<i>You have to!</i>

182
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:50,480
But…

183
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:54,440
How are you going to do it?
Your mom's challenge is huge, Cent.

184
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:57,520
I guess I'll make some kind of app
for people to use on their phones.

185
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:01,320
I'll focus on the food sector.

186
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:04,800
It's closest to Mom.
One month for the app, and it'll be done.

187
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:08,120
But I'll need Thai people
to help collect info.

188
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:12,320
Okay! I have some Thai friends
who could help.

189
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:16,280
Wait. You are Thai.

190
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:19,280
<i>Don't you have any friends?</i>

191
00:13:23,520 --> 00:13:25,400
Almost forgot! I totally forgot!

192
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:27,640
I'm your only friend.

193
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:34,200
And your friend, who is that?

194
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:36,400
I can help, no problem.

195
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:38,520
I've wanted to meet Mr. Cent
for a long time.

196
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:42,320
I heard he's quiet and keeps to himself.
Finally, I'll get to meet him.

197
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:45,720
I'm free Sunday evening.

198
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:48,640
Tell him to tell me where to meet,
and I'll go.

199
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:03,640
Fuang!

200
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:05,360
Yes, Mom!

201
00:14:13,680 --> 00:14:15,240
Wow!

202
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:19,200
- Smells amazing!
- You've been a handful.

203
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:20,600
Here.

204
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:22,160
Can I taste it?

205
00:14:22,760 --> 00:14:23,640
What about your dad?

206
00:14:23,720 --> 00:14:26,000
- Huh?
- I'll go call him.

207
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:29,720
Okay. Hurry. The food's almost ready!

208
00:14:34,280 --> 00:14:36,200
I'm not hungry yet.
You and Mom can eat first.

209
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:37,720
But if you skip meals,

210
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:41,520
you might get gastritis or acid reflux.

211
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:47,080
Then you'll have to see a doctor,
and we'd spend a lot.

212
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:52,720
Eat now, Dad. Better than getting sick
and paying for expensive treatment.

213
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:56,760
Private hospitals cost a fortune,
and public ones

214
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:59,160
- make you wait forever.
- Enough!

215
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:06,920
You're really good at coming up
with reasons to convince people.

216
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:09,520
I got a lot of it from Mom.

217
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:16,280
Getting it from Mom is good.
She's talented.

218
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:20,000
If it were from me, it wouldn't matter.

219
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:26,080
- <i>Fuang.</i>
<i>- Yes?</i>

220
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:29,560
I'm thinking of designing a bag
that looks younger.

221
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:33,760
I want to tap into the teen market.
Maybe I'll make more sales.

222
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:37,800
But kids like me don't have money, Mom.

223
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:41,240
I was thinking moms
could buy it for their kids.

224
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:44,000
Just an idea for now.

225
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:47,720
Do you think it'll work?
My funds are limited.

226
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:51,000
Then I'll get a part-time job.

227
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:53,680
Once I earn some money,
I can give it to you to invest more.

228
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:55,800
- Good idea?
- Wow! Sadhu!

229
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:57,400
Hope you get a job soon.

230
00:15:58,000 --> 00:15:59,640
- Sadhu!
- Bless you!

231
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:02,680
I'm full.

232
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:10,160
Ugh!

233
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:12,880
He just can't let go of the past.

234
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:15,480
When will he move on and start working?

235
00:16:16,080 --> 00:16:20,200
Mom, calm down. Don't get worked up.
Eat before it gets cold.

236
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:22,000
Here, eat this.

237
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:24,000
Eight-minute boiled egg.

238
00:16:25,920 --> 00:16:27,920
He never cheers me on.

239
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:39,760
<i>I called your cell. You didn't pick up,</i>
<i>so I'm calling your home.</i>

240
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:42,800
I'm eating.

241
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:44,880
Is it urgent, Peace?

242
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:48,120
<i>Are you free Sunday evening?</i>

243
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:50,280
<i>Let's have dinner.</i>

244
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:54,640
You have to be free. Back when
you were in school, you always weren't.

245
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:57,600
Now that you've graduated, no excuses.

246
00:17:05,079 --> 00:17:07,560
Okay then. So…

247
00:17:08,920 --> 00:17:10,000
Sunday evening?

248
00:17:10,079 --> 00:17:11,920
Yes, see you.

249
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:14,240
Okay, see you then.

250
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:22,040
Dinner with Peace!

251
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:29,640
Peace!

252
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:32,400
<i>Don't tell Franc.</i>

253
00:17:32,480 --> 00:17:33,880
Don't tell Franc.

254
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:37,040
Why not?

255
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:41,440
If you want to know, just ask him.

256
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:46,320
Maybe our friend caused some trouble,
so he feels awkward and wants to avoid it.

257
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:49,320
If you're worried about being polite,
just ask him face to face.

258
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:53,960
Hey! Look at the photos.
What should I wear?

259
00:17:57,920 --> 00:18:00,120
Whatever, just wear it.

260
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:03,840
<i>But what's up with you?</i>
<i>You're suddenly stressed about clothes.</i>

261
00:18:05,040 --> 00:18:07,680
I haven't been to an event in ages.
I don't know what to wear.

262
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:11,760
Hey, Fuang. I've got something
to tell you. But if I tell you,

263
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:14,080
don't be upset.

264
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:17,160
- What?
- Peace invited me too.

265
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:18,520
Oh.

266
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:21,440
But if you and Peace
want to go on a date together,

267
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:24,680
just tell me. I won't go.

268
00:18:24,760 --> 00:18:25,760
No way!

269
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:29,520
I'm not planning
to go on a date or anything.

270
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:33,360
<i>I'm just dressing properly</i>
<i>for the invitation.</i>

271
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:36,280
Just dressing up properly
for the invitation, huh?

272
00:18:37,360 --> 00:18:42,040
Fuang, what's going on
between you and Peace?

273
00:18:42,120 --> 00:18:43,960
<i>Any status updates yet?</i>

274
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:45,240
Not yet.

275
00:18:46,080 --> 00:18:50,200
When I was in school, I was busy,
and Peace was busy too.

276
00:18:50,280 --> 00:18:53,080
Now that I've graduated, I'll…

277
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:56,000
I'll give myself some time.

278
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:57,640
<i>Give yourself some time?</i>

279
00:18:57,720 --> 00:19:00,400
Hey! But don't tell anyone yet.

280
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:02,800
<i>Why not?</i>

281
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:04,480
I don't know how to act!

282
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:08,000
And I'm not sure how he feels either.

283
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:11,520
I'll make it clear first,
then let them find out.

284
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:17,720
Oh! Do you think Peace
invited Bonus and Pound too?

285
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,600
You honked so loud.

286
00:19:20,680 --> 00:19:22,280
Thought she wouldn't notice you're here?

287
00:19:23,320 --> 00:19:24,360
I'm here!

288
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,440
- Hey.
- Wow!

289
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:29,280
What?

290
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:32,080
You look cute!
Look, she's even wearing a skirt!

291
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:33,480
- Yeah.
- Right.

292
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:36,880
You didn't know that Peace
booked a som tam restaurant, right?

293
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:38,920
- Som tam restaurant?
- Yep!

294
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,600
Did he tell you not to tell Franc?

295
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:42,520
- Yes.
- Yeah.

296
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,360
I bet Franc just texted.

297
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:47,120
- Don't read it!
- Don't read it!

298
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:55,560
Why isn't anyone reading this?

299
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:02,600
It says the place is just up ahead, right?

300
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:04,120
Yeah.

301
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:06,560
- Hungry yet?
- I'm starting to get hungry.

302
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:08,520
- Looks like it's not far.
- I'm hungry.

303
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:11,800
Pound, why did Peace pick this restaurant?

304
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:14,840
Totally out of character.
He usually takes us somewhere fancy.

305
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:16,280
Yeah, you're right.

306
00:20:19,520 --> 00:20:22,560
Pound, I left something in the car.
Can I get the keys?

307
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:25,760
What? Lock the car too, alright?

308
00:20:25,840 --> 00:20:27,000
Want me to go with you?

309
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:29,280
It's fine. You guys go ahead.
I'll catch up.

310
00:20:29,360 --> 00:20:30,600
Okay.

311
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:32,760
Hey, don't forget to lock the car!

312
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:35,000
- She knows already!
- Follow along, okay?

313
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:36,720
I'm just worried.

314
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,360
- He's really skilled.
- A business?

315
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:39,880
- Yeah.
- What do you want to do?

316
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:40,920
Oh!

317
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:44,160
- Four cheese durian.
- Four cheese?

318
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:46,400
- How's that? Nowadays…
- Wait, isn't four cheese…?

319
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:48,600
- Pizza!
- Yeah. That's the business idea.

320
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:52,400
I just came up with it
and wanted to pitch it to him.

321
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:55,000
- Make sure the pitch is appropriate.
- Yeah.

322
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:03,800
Mr. Cent!

323
00:21:05,760 --> 00:21:06,760
Cent?

324
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:29,840
I'm Peace, Kenji's friend.
These are my juniors.

325
00:21:30,440 --> 00:21:33,480
Pound, Bonus, Yuan, and Fuang.

326
00:21:36,160 --> 00:21:37,440
- Hello.
- Hello.

327
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:42,440
- Please, have a seat.
- I'd like a separate table to talk.

328
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,000
All the tables are full.

329
00:21:49,640 --> 00:21:50,480
Let's split the tables.

330
00:21:51,520 --> 00:21:54,560
Oh, split the tables.

331
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:56,080
I'll help separate the tables.

332
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:58,960
I'll sit next to you.

333
00:21:59,040 --> 00:22:00,560
Okay.

334
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:03,200
Please, go ahead.

335
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:05,640
Thanks.

336
00:22:06,840 --> 00:22:09,200
- It's nothing. I just separated them.
- No.

337
00:22:10,240 --> 00:22:13,640
Thanks for asking the motorbike rider
to move so that there's parking space.

338
00:22:14,440 --> 00:22:15,520
Oh.

339
00:22:16,640 --> 00:22:17,520
You're welcome.

340
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:22,880
Please, have a seat.

341
00:22:23,840 --> 00:22:26,160
Which motorbike?

342
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:27,200
I'll tell you later.

343
00:22:27,280 --> 00:22:28,920
- Just tell us!
- Go ahead!

344
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:31,360
- Tell us what happened.
- Hurry up, I want to know!

345
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:34,360
I'll keep it short. This won't take long.

346
00:22:35,560 --> 00:22:38,960
Okay. I'll order food
for these guys first then.

347
00:22:40,040 --> 00:22:41,600
- Go ahead.
- Okay.

348
00:22:43,520 --> 00:22:46,280
- Let's scan the menu and order.
- Okay.

349
00:22:47,120 --> 00:22:49,160
You can eat anything, right? No allergies?

350
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:51,040
Hey, you'll like this.

351
00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:52,000
What is it?

352
00:22:52,080 --> 00:22:54,000
- Four Cheese Som Tam!
- They have that?

353
00:22:54,080 --> 00:22:55,960
- Of course not!
- You guys!

354
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:04,880
Hey, there's more food.

355
00:23:05,560 --> 00:23:06,640
Thank you.

356
00:23:06,720 --> 00:23:08,240
What kind of soup is this?

357
00:23:08,320 --> 00:23:09,840
I need someone to collect

358
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:12,520
and organize data for the app.

359
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:16,240
It's just an app. Why do it yourself?

360
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:18,440
You could hire a skilled team.

361
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:21,760
It's personal. I won't explain why.

362
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:26,880
Got it! If you're doing it yourself,
it'll be done fast.

363
00:23:26,960 --> 00:23:29,040
What kind of assistant do you want?

364
00:23:29,640 --> 00:23:32,520
Someone who understands immediately.
I hate repeating myself

365
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:34,360
or explaining too much.

366
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:37,320
Okay.

367
00:23:38,080 --> 00:23:40,920
Thank you. I'll cover all the expenses.

368
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:43,080
This meal's on me.

369
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:45,880
- It's okay.
- I don't like repeating myself.

370
00:23:48,040 --> 00:23:50,600
- Well then, thank you!
- Thank you.

371
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:52,360
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

372
00:23:52,440 --> 00:23:53,840
Thank you.

373
00:23:59,960 --> 00:24:02,600
- Peace, I think…
- Huh?

374
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:06,160
- Your friend is kinda weird.
- Oh.

375
00:24:06,240 --> 00:24:09,600
He's my friend's friend.
He's a techie. That's just how they are.

376
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:11,720
A bit quirky, but I'm used to it.

377
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:14,360
Techies? What's that?

378
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:17,440
People who work with computers,
doing programming.

379
00:24:17,520 --> 00:24:20,120
This place is also run by his mom.

380
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:21,760
- Oh.
- I see.

381
00:24:22,400 --> 00:24:27,120
No wonder the place
seems ordinary, but also modern.

382
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:28,880
Take that, for example.

383
00:24:29,400 --> 00:24:30,440
See that?

384
00:24:30,520 --> 00:24:33,400
You have to scan to order.

385
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:35,320
It's totally mismatched.

386
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:37,560
- Let's eat!
- Come on.

387
00:24:37,640 --> 00:24:39,240
Time to eat!

388
00:24:46,920 --> 00:24:48,600
SOM TAM PALACE

389
00:24:57,680 --> 00:24:59,760
ORDER NO. 168 - TABLE NO. 45
ORDER NO. 169 - TABLE NO. 26

390
00:24:59,840 --> 00:25:01,000
THE PALACE OF FLAVORS, PICK WHAT YOU LIKE
SOM TAM VARIETIES

391
00:25:08,760 --> 00:25:09,600
Pong!

392
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:10,600
Yes!

393
00:25:16,280 --> 00:25:17,360
Mom.

394
00:25:18,880 --> 00:25:19,760
What?

395
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:23,200
I've set up a stock check system
in the POS.

396
00:25:23,280 --> 00:25:24,800
When a customer orders,

397
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:27,840
it automatically deducts the ingredients.

398
00:25:27,920 --> 00:25:30,560
I set an alert for five portions left.

399
00:25:30,640 --> 00:25:33,280
For example, today you prepared
50 batches of papaya for som tam.

400
00:25:33,360 --> 00:25:35,920
You've already used 45,
so you've got five left.

401
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:39,560
So, in short, you're saying
my papaya is almost gone?

402
00:25:50,200 --> 00:25:51,520
- Peace.
- Huh?

403
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:54,560
Why did you call us here?
And why couldn't we tell Franc?

404
00:25:56,960 --> 00:25:59,120
Did she do something
to cause trouble for you?

405
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:02,320
No! Alright, everyone.

406
00:26:02,400 --> 00:26:04,000
The reason I didn't want Franc to know

407
00:26:05,320 --> 00:26:08,440
is because I want it to be a surprise.

408
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:10,880
- A surprise?
- A surprise?

409
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:13,040
A surprise for what?

410
00:26:14,320 --> 00:26:15,960
I'm going to propose to Franc.

411
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:21,200
- Propose?
- Propose?

412
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:23,320
Yes.

413
00:26:25,840 --> 00:26:27,200
Propose?

414
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:33,440
Yes.

415
00:26:39,880 --> 00:26:41,360
That really is a surprise.

416
00:26:51,320 --> 00:26:55,360
Peace, how long
have you been together with Franc?

417
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:58,120
Three years already.

418
00:26:59,280 --> 00:27:02,360
Then why haven't you ever told us?

419
00:27:02,440 --> 00:27:06,800
Franc and I agreed
we wanted it to happen slowly.

420
00:27:06,880 --> 00:27:10,200
Didn't want you all to focus on us,
so we've kept it low-key.

421
00:27:11,040 --> 00:27:15,400
Low-key indeed.
Three years and nobody knew.

422
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:18,680
Alright.

423
00:27:20,040 --> 00:27:23,760
Anyway, congratulations in advance!

424
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:26,320
So, how can we help?

425
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:32,280
I want all of us
to help organize the surprise.

426
00:27:32,880 --> 00:27:34,120
When?

427
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:36,400
Tomorrow.

428
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:41,200
Your birthday?

429
00:27:49,800 --> 00:27:51,360
I'll go to the bathroom.

430
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:12,760
I'm sorry.

431
00:28:12,840 --> 00:28:16,280
SOM TAM PALACE

432
00:28:58,240 --> 00:28:59,480
TOO BAD, ME AND THE OTHERS
ARE HAVING FUN FOR YOU

433
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:43,680
Are you tired from all that crying?

434
00:29:52,520 --> 00:29:55,240
I'm okay.

435
00:29:55,840 --> 00:29:57,200
Okay's good.

436
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:07,840
Best not to fool yourself.

437
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:38,120
Seriously, I still don't get

438
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:40,680
how Peace and Franc
managed to keep it secret.

439
00:30:40,760 --> 00:30:43,720
I'm the closest to Peace,
yet I still couldn't tell!

440
00:30:44,600 --> 00:30:47,800
- But I could tell a long time ago.
- Really?

441
00:30:49,560 --> 00:30:52,240
Think about it.

442
00:30:52,920 --> 00:30:55,600
Lately, whenever we meet up,

443
00:30:55,680 --> 00:30:58,160
these two always arrive together.

444
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:02,520
And they even wear matching outfits.

445
00:31:03,480 --> 00:31:04,720
Matching outfits?

446
00:31:05,320 --> 00:31:08,040
I'm not trying to be nosy, okay?

447
00:31:08,120 --> 00:31:10,840
I just took screenshots.

448
00:31:12,560 --> 00:31:14,000
I'll show you.

449
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:22,320
Here, look.

450
00:31:23,400 --> 00:31:24,400
Clear enough?

451
00:31:26,680 --> 00:31:29,200
Yeah, now it's clear!

452
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:32,440
Your curiosity really shows.

453
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:35,080
Hey, Pound!

454
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:37,480
It's called being observant.

455
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:41,320
But why didn't you ever tell us?

456
00:31:41,400 --> 00:31:44,560
I didn't want to meddle
in other people's business.

457
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:47,520
‪Oh! So you weren't meddling at all?

458
00:31:47,600 --> 00:31:49,440
- Do you want it again?
- Enough!

459
00:31:49,520 --> 00:31:52,520
Besides Peace and Franc,

460
00:31:52,600 --> 00:31:54,520
is anyone secretly liking
or dating someone?

461
00:31:54,600 --> 00:31:56,480
You gotta tell me. I hate surprises.

462
00:31:58,440 --> 00:32:02,680
Oh! I left something at the restaurant.
I'll be right back.

463
00:32:02,760 --> 00:32:03,760
Hey.

464
00:32:05,960 --> 00:32:07,760
What's up with Fuang today?

465
00:32:08,960 --> 00:32:11,200
She's so distracted,
keeps forgetting stuff.

466
00:32:21,600 --> 00:32:22,920
Mr. Cent!

467
00:32:24,440 --> 00:32:26,160
The customer left something behind.

468
00:32:26,800 --> 00:32:28,000
Alright.

469
00:32:36,160 --> 00:32:37,600
SRIYAN BEEF MEATBALLS

470
00:32:51,760 --> 00:32:52,960
Oh.

471
00:32:53,040 --> 00:32:56,040
SRIYAN BEEF MEATBALLS

472
00:32:57,160 --> 00:32:58,000
Whoa.

473
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:12,400
Excuse me.

474
00:33:12,480 --> 00:33:14,880
Could you please move your bike?

475
00:33:14,960 --> 00:33:17,440
Whoever's in that car
might want to eat noodles here.

476
00:33:18,440 --> 00:33:19,800
That way, she'll get another customer.

477
00:33:19,880 --> 00:33:22,040
That's right. That way,
I can sell more noodles.

478
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:24,960
Just keep going then.

479
00:33:26,360 --> 00:33:27,520
Thank you.

480
00:34:00,320 --> 00:34:01,600
<i>What a surprise! Didn't see that coming.</i>

481
00:34:02,160 --> 00:34:05,080
Once she says yes, when's the wedding?

482
00:34:06,040 --> 00:34:07,320
It depends on Franc.

483
00:34:08,560 --> 00:34:11,600
When she's ready, we'll just get married!

484
00:34:12,760 --> 00:34:15,360
- Just like that?
- I don't want to wait any longer.

485
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:17,639
Let's go.

486
00:34:17,719 --> 00:34:19,960
My brother's getting married!

487
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:24,280
It's mine.

488
00:34:31,199 --> 00:34:33,199
SOM TAM PALACE

489
00:34:37,040 --> 00:34:38,920
Thank you for keeping it for me.

490
00:35:34,360 --> 00:35:36,240
Yuan! Still not going home?

491
00:35:37,400 --> 00:35:39,600
I left my bag in the room,
and the door closed too fast.

492
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:41,720
Anything important in it?

493
00:35:42,560 --> 00:35:47,560
Just my wallet. I don't have money on me.
Don't know how to get home.

494
00:35:48,760 --> 00:35:49,880
Let's go home together.

495
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:54,200
Come on, the driver's on the way.

496
00:35:57,280 --> 00:35:58,120
Hurry!

497
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:16,880
M.S.

498
00:38:13,960 --> 00:38:16,800
Cent. This evening,
take me to visit a friend, will you?

499
00:38:16,880 --> 00:38:18,160
Isn't Pong free?

500
00:38:18,760 --> 00:38:20,400
Pong has to mind the shop.

501
00:38:21,720 --> 00:38:25,000
Why? Can't you just take me
to see a friend?

502
00:38:26,800 --> 00:38:29,480
This friend's been around forever,
you know.

503
00:38:29,560 --> 00:38:32,520
We've known each other
since she went to study in the U.S.

504
00:38:32,600 --> 00:38:34,560
We haven't met since she returned.

505
00:38:35,840 --> 00:38:37,440
Finally, we tracked each other down.

506
00:38:39,080 --> 00:38:40,360
Found her on Facebook, huh?

507
00:38:40,440 --> 00:38:42,960
You know everything, don't you?

508
00:38:43,760 --> 00:38:46,800
So, how's the work I gave you going?

509
00:38:46,880 --> 00:38:48,720
- I'm getting someone to help.
- Hey!

510
00:38:48,800 --> 00:38:51,600
Just assisting.
I'm doing it myself, don't worry.

511
00:39:01,600 --> 00:39:04,360
Fuang!

512
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:06,840
You have a visitor!

513
00:39:07,880 --> 00:39:09,600
Who is it?

514
00:39:09,680 --> 00:39:11,360
It's me!

515
00:39:24,280 --> 00:39:25,560
Time to wake up!

516
00:39:30,640 --> 00:39:31,480
Thank you, Mom.

517
00:39:32,680 --> 00:39:34,080
Make yourself comfortable.

518
00:39:34,160 --> 00:39:37,040
We've got snacks in the kitchen.
Help yourself.

519
00:39:37,120 --> 00:39:38,400
Thank you.

520
00:39:39,040 --> 00:39:42,080
Oh, Mom! As for the bag I ordered,
I'll take it with me.

521
00:39:42,160 --> 00:39:45,160
I'll also throw in a matching keychain
for the bag.

522
00:39:45,240 --> 00:39:46,800
Thanks so much!

523
00:39:46,880 --> 00:39:48,680
I'll go prepare the bag for you.

524
00:39:48,760 --> 00:39:50,240
- Thank you.
- Sure.

525
00:39:52,760 --> 00:39:55,800
Coming so early, all because of the bag?

526
00:39:57,480 --> 00:40:00,960
I came because I'm worried about you.

527
00:40:01,680 --> 00:40:03,600
You didn't pick up
or reply to my messages.

528
00:40:03,680 --> 00:40:05,720
I called 15 times.

529
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:07,080
See?

530
00:40:07,160 --> 00:40:09,080
Wow, you called so many times!

531
00:40:10,960 --> 00:40:13,760
Just say it already, I'm sleepy.

532
00:40:15,480 --> 00:40:18,320
Pound posted
about Peace's birthday party tonight.

533
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:21,440
I saw you didn't respond,
so I came to ask if you're going.

534
00:40:22,520 --> 00:40:24,000
Yeah, I'll go.

535
00:40:27,800 --> 00:40:29,840
And yesterday, everyone just disappeared.

536
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:32,120
I messaged, but no one replied.

537
00:40:32,840 --> 00:40:34,640
Are you hiding something from me?

538
00:40:39,600 --> 00:40:42,240
Answer me! Are you hiding something?

539
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:46,640
What about you?
Are you hiding something from me?

540
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:52,240
Yes!

541
00:40:52,320 --> 00:40:56,800
Lots, actually. But I'm not telling you.
If I did, you'd know everything.

542
00:40:58,400 --> 00:40:59,840
What the heck?

543
00:41:00,480 --> 00:41:03,600
Your friends can't keep secrets from you,
but you can do it to them?

544
00:41:04,200 --> 00:41:07,440
Yeah, especially you.
Don't keep secrets from me.

545
00:41:09,160 --> 00:41:11,360
You're the friend I trust the most.

546
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:15,240
And I know someone like you can't lie.

547
00:41:18,120 --> 00:41:20,520
So, are you hiding something? Tell me!

548
00:41:20,600 --> 00:41:24,440
Who's hiding something from you?
I didn't reply

549
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:27,360
because I was swamped with work yesterday.

550
00:41:28,360 --> 00:41:30,040
As for the others,

551
00:41:30,120 --> 00:41:32,480
I don't know why they didn't respond.
Ask them yourself.

552
00:41:33,080 --> 00:41:35,400
What work? You've got work already?

553
00:41:35,480 --> 00:41:39,760
Just general design jobs I applied for.

554
00:41:41,840 --> 00:41:43,400
My stickers…

555
00:41:44,120 --> 00:41:45,520
keep getting rejected.

556
00:41:46,320 --> 00:41:48,160
Come on.

557
00:41:48,240 --> 00:41:51,320
It's just the beginning. Don't give up.

558
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:53,960
You're talented. I know you can do it.

559
00:41:56,200 --> 00:41:59,120
- Be confident!
- Yeah!

560
00:42:00,600 --> 00:42:01,800
Feeling touched?

561
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:04,800
Idiot, I'm sleepy. Go away!

562
00:42:04,880 --> 00:42:08,160
It's good that you're alright,
then I won't worry.

563
00:42:08,240 --> 00:42:10,920
I'll get ready, and we'll meet tonight.

564
00:42:17,760 --> 00:42:18,640
Hey, Franc!

565
00:42:26,920 --> 00:42:29,520
Go on out and shut the door.
I'm going to sleep.

566
00:42:30,760 --> 00:42:33,080
That's it? You made it sound so dramatic.

567
00:42:33,840 --> 00:42:35,200
See you tonight. Bye!

568
00:42:48,600 --> 00:42:50,000
<i>Hey, how's it going?</i>

569
00:42:51,080 --> 00:42:52,920
Franc just left a moment ago.

570
00:42:53,840 --> 00:42:55,080
Did she notice anything?

571
00:42:57,200 --> 00:42:59,920
Nope, she's just happy as usual.

572
00:43:04,080 --> 00:43:05,280
<i>Fuang.</i>

573
00:43:07,320 --> 00:43:08,880
You're really okay, right?

574
00:43:13,360 --> 00:43:15,160
Yeah. Talk to you later.

575
00:43:41,080 --> 00:43:44,400
Tonight I'm closing the whole place.
There will be 4-5 dummy tables set up.

576
00:43:44,480 --> 00:43:47,480
The behind-the-scenes team

577
00:43:47,560 --> 00:43:49,560
will hide cameras around here.

578
00:43:50,480 --> 00:43:52,120
When Franc arrives

579
00:43:52,200 --> 00:43:55,160
- and we're chatting here,
- Yes.

580
00:43:55,240 --> 00:43:57,840
the musicians will start playing.

581
00:43:59,040 --> 00:44:00,760
- Got it. I understand.
- Okay.

582
00:44:01,440 --> 00:44:03,280
After a while,

583
00:44:03,920 --> 00:44:06,480
this kid will come

584
00:44:06,560 --> 00:44:10,320
and guide Franc's hand.
This part is crucial.

585
00:44:10,400 --> 00:44:11,360
Okay.

586
00:44:11,440 --> 00:44:15,440
Everyone has to help build it up
so Franc agrees to move.

587
00:44:15,520 --> 00:44:18,480
Then Franc will walk over to here.

588
00:44:21,120 --> 00:44:23,440
And you'll come out
looking cool right here.

589
00:44:24,040 --> 00:44:26,040
- Exactly!
- So cool, bro.

590
00:44:26,120 --> 00:44:27,920
- Got it?
- Yeah.

591
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:29,920
Alright, make sure
to brief the others too.

592
00:44:30,760 --> 00:44:33,160
I will do that. Hey, Peace!

593
00:44:36,480 --> 00:44:38,640
Honestly, at first, I thought

594
00:44:38,720 --> 00:44:40,960
you were secretly seeing Fuang, not Franc.

595
00:44:41,760 --> 00:44:44,920
I mean, I thought
you were closer to her than to Franc.

596
00:44:47,360 --> 00:44:50,640
Before college, that's true.

597
00:44:51,480 --> 00:44:54,360
But once Fuang started university,
we kind of drifted apart.

598
00:44:56,360 --> 00:44:58,960
Are you the only one
thinking that you've drifted apart?

599
00:44:59,040 --> 00:45:01,360
Did you ever ask her
if she felt the same way?

600
00:45:04,080 --> 00:45:08,440
Even if Fuang never said anything,
she's been showing it.

601
00:45:09,360 --> 00:45:10,680
You really can't see it?

602
00:45:16,240 --> 00:45:19,840
I'll leave you to watch over things here.
I'll be back.

603
00:45:21,360 --> 00:45:22,760
Hey, wait!

604
00:45:24,680 --> 00:45:25,680
Peace!

605
00:45:42,520 --> 00:45:43,720
Just woke up?

606
00:45:46,640 --> 00:45:47,880
Peace.

607
00:45:59,480 --> 00:46:02,120
I've been up for a while.

608
00:46:03,880 --> 00:46:07,160
What's up? Why didn't
you tell me you were coming?

609
00:46:07,880 --> 00:46:09,640
I have something to apologize for.

610
00:46:12,360 --> 00:46:13,800
I'm sorry

611
00:46:14,720 --> 00:46:16,640
I never told you that I'm dating Franc.

612
00:46:21,080 --> 00:46:23,920
- I mean--
- You don't have to apologize.

613
00:46:29,120 --> 00:46:31,880
It's your private life.

614
00:46:33,320 --> 00:46:36,640
Whether you tell me or not,

615
00:46:38,560 --> 00:46:39,920
that's your choice.

616
00:46:43,480 --> 00:46:45,040
I'm okay.

617
00:46:48,040 --> 00:46:50,520
I'll go take a shower.

618
00:46:51,880 --> 00:46:52,880
Fuang!

619
00:46:56,960 --> 00:47:00,240
The reason I felt upset
is because back then…

620
00:47:02,480 --> 00:47:04,360
Before you started university,

621
00:47:05,880 --> 00:47:07,680
we were really close.

622
00:47:10,520 --> 00:47:13,000
But once you went to university,
you drifted away.

623
00:47:15,200 --> 00:47:19,040
And that's when I got closer to Franc.

624
00:47:24,080 --> 00:47:26,920
I just want you to understand,
so I came to explain.

625
00:47:31,240 --> 00:47:32,400
We…

626
00:47:34,160 --> 00:47:35,960
We can still be friends, right?

627
00:47:51,320 --> 00:47:52,520
Of course!

628
00:47:55,720 --> 00:47:57,840
We've always been friends.

629
00:48:03,640 --> 00:48:06,360
Okay, hearing that makes me feel relieved.

630
00:48:08,160 --> 00:48:11,480
Today is your special day with Franc.

631
00:48:12,400 --> 00:48:13,760
So don't worry.

632
00:48:15,600 --> 00:48:18,440
I'll go shower

633
00:48:18,520 --> 00:48:21,080
and get ready,
then I'll help with the event.

634
00:48:24,480 --> 00:48:25,640
Thank you.

635
00:48:28,200 --> 00:48:29,520
Truly, thank you.

636
00:48:37,640 --> 00:48:38,840
Just a sec.

637
00:48:40,840 --> 00:48:41,960
Hello, Miss Kwang?

638
00:48:43,600 --> 00:48:44,920
Yes.

639
00:48:45,760 --> 00:48:49,320
Tonight? Can't we postpone it?

640
00:48:52,000 --> 00:48:52,960
Okay.

641
00:48:53,040 --> 00:48:54,680
Yes, thank you.

642
00:48:57,440 --> 00:48:58,800
I'm in trouble.

643
00:48:59,960 --> 00:49:02,840
My secretary just called.

644
00:49:02,920 --> 00:49:05,640
Someone from the ministry
scheduled a meeting this evening.

645
00:49:06,520 --> 00:49:08,880
I probably won't be able to prep
for the event this afternoon.

646
00:49:09,600 --> 00:49:13,960
It's okay. Me and the others
will handle it.

647
00:49:14,640 --> 00:49:16,960
Pound already shared
the rough schedule on Line.

648
00:49:20,400 --> 00:49:23,360
I'll leave it in your hands then.

649
00:49:27,280 --> 00:49:28,640
See you tonight.

650
00:49:42,120 --> 00:49:43,200
Peace.

651
00:49:50,440 --> 00:49:52,160
I have something for you.

652
00:50:00,640 --> 00:50:02,520
<i>I made this a while ago,</i>

653
00:50:03,640 --> 00:50:05,920
<i>but never got the chance to give it.</i>

654
00:50:08,360 --> 00:50:09,960
<i>Today's your birthday.</i>

655
00:50:10,040 --> 00:50:11,320
HAPPY PEACE DAY - WISHING YOU HAPPINESS
GOOD HEALTH, AND MANY FUN TRIPS

656
00:50:11,400 --> 00:50:15,640
<i>And it's an important day.</i>
<i>I want you to have it as a gift.</i>

657
00:50:56,160 --> 00:50:57,120
Fuang.

658
00:50:59,680 --> 00:51:00,880
Fuang, my dear.

659
00:51:10,920 --> 00:51:12,200
Mom.

660
00:51:22,520 --> 00:51:25,160
Do you want to tell me what's going on?

661
00:51:30,560 --> 00:51:34,280
Peace is getting married

662
00:51:35,360 --> 00:51:37,840
- to Franc, Mom.
- Oh!

663
00:51:38,520 --> 00:51:39,920
I thought you and…

664
00:51:40,000 --> 00:51:42,400
Peace and I are just friends.

665
00:51:43,000 --> 00:51:46,720
Just friends? Then why are you crying?

666
00:51:53,040 --> 00:51:54,680
I don't know, Mom.

667
00:51:56,000 --> 00:51:57,240
It's okay, dear.

668
00:51:59,520 --> 00:52:03,040
Sometimes we don't really understand
our own feelings.

669
00:52:04,280 --> 00:52:08,200
If you feel like crying, just let it out.
You'll feel better afterward.

670
00:52:26,120 --> 00:52:28,760
Tears are actually helpful, Fuang.

671
00:52:30,360 --> 00:52:34,560
They help block dust
and even reduce infections.

672
00:52:36,080 --> 00:52:39,800
Mom, that was

673
00:52:40,400 --> 00:52:42,880
such a cool thing to say to comfort me.

674
00:52:44,480 --> 00:52:45,640
My dear.

675
00:53:00,560 --> 00:53:03,800
I've seen what people posted.
It's way more extravagant than this.

676
00:53:03,880 --> 00:53:06,480
Hey, we better help him out.

677
00:53:06,560 --> 00:53:09,320
I heard he got called into a meeting.
He's probably panicking.

678
00:53:10,080 --> 00:53:12,920
Really? Do you think
Peace will make it on time?

679
00:53:17,040 --> 00:53:18,200
That's Franc for sure.

680
00:53:21,120 --> 00:53:23,520
She asked where we are. She's on her way.

681
00:53:27,840 --> 00:53:31,840
I'll go check the hallway to see
if they've finished putting up the photos.

682
00:53:31,920 --> 00:53:34,920
Good, then I can report to him
that Franc is coming.

683
00:54:09,800 --> 00:54:13,200
<i>Jump in!</i>

684
00:54:13,280 --> 00:54:14,200
I'm ready!

685
00:54:14,280 --> 00:54:16,280
- Take off your shoes and get in!
- Come on!

686
00:54:16,960 --> 00:54:18,240
Hurry, get in the pool!

687
00:54:18,320 --> 00:54:20,720
Jump in!

688
00:54:20,800 --> 00:54:22,480
Whoa!

689
00:54:22,560 --> 00:54:25,520
Look over here, Pound, Yuan!

690
00:54:31,880 --> 00:54:33,040
If you're not okay,

691
00:54:35,520 --> 00:54:37,280
you don't have to stay tonight.

692
00:54:38,600 --> 00:54:41,640
- Hey, I--
- You don't need to say you're okay,

693
00:54:42,880 --> 00:54:44,480
because I won't believe it.

694
00:54:47,200 --> 00:54:49,320
I'm not saying I'm okay.

695
00:54:51,080 --> 00:54:52,680
But I will say,

696
00:54:53,560 --> 00:54:57,720
this morning, Peace came to my house.

697
00:54:59,640 --> 00:55:00,760
And…

698
00:55:02,200 --> 00:55:03,760
we cleared things up.

699
00:55:04,560 --> 00:55:06,280
Cleared what up?

700
00:55:08,200 --> 00:55:09,360
Well…

701
00:55:12,840 --> 00:55:16,600
We're still just friends, like before.

702
00:55:20,440 --> 00:55:22,360
But now I know…

703
00:55:26,120 --> 00:55:27,800
The one who's really right for Peace

704
00:55:29,680 --> 00:55:30,920
is Franc.

705
00:55:43,920 --> 00:55:46,280
Alright, then I won't give you the shares.

706
00:55:46,360 --> 00:55:48,360
- What? Mom!
- It's time to take your medicine!

707
00:55:48,440 --> 00:55:49,400
- Not now, Pong!
- Go away, Pong!

708
00:55:56,960 --> 00:55:59,760
I'm not the type to steal from my friends.

709
00:55:59,840 --> 00:56:02,200
Fuang is my best friend.

710
00:56:02,280 --> 00:56:05,040
If I had known,
I would've stayed away from him!

711
00:56:05,120 --> 00:56:09,400
I'm speechless. I'm stunned,
shocked, and so happy!

712
00:56:09,480 --> 00:56:11,400
Thank you!

713
00:56:12,800 --> 00:56:18,080
But are you sure Cent
will accept me as his assistant?

714
00:57:00,760 --> 00:57:04,000
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
